The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Boy punches teacher

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Krishnagar, Jan. 18: A Class XII student of a school in Nadia today beat up a teacher who slapped him for using foul language on the campus.

 Panna Bhattacharjee, a philosophy teacher of Dignagar High School in the Kotwali police station area, about 80 km from Calcutta, was punched in the face and kicked.

 Bleeding profusely, he was taken to Shaktinagar Hospital. The teacher lost a tooth and his nose was injured, said a police officer.

 Tapas Mukherjee, the 18-year-old student, was apparently using foul language while talking to a classmate. Bhattacharjee said he was taking a class around 1.30 pm when he heard Tapas and some of his classmates talking in the corridor. Tapas was using foul language. I repeatedly asked him not to do so but he did not pay any heed. I could not control myself and slapped him, said Bhattacharjee.

 An officer of Kotwali police station said Tapas took the teacher by the collar and started punching him on the face.

 The schools teacher-in-charge Asit Das and Bhattacharjee lodged a police complaint. But later, Bhattacharjee requested the police not to initiate any action against Tapas as he was a candidate for this years higher secondary exams. However, the school authorities expelled Tapas.

 Taunt suicide

 Unable to bear taunts by his wife that he was not doing much to maintain his family, a 23-year-old youth who lived in his in-laws house allegedly committed suicide in Nadias Krishnagunj yesterday.

 Police said Deb Adhikary consumed pesticide after his wife taunted him on Tuesday while he was playing badminton with his friends. Some villagers found Deb writhing in pain and rushed him to a health centre, where he died.




